// Content Sprint 6.
window.CONTENT_SPRINT_6 = {"seller-lifecycle":{"summary":"Manage each Seller through a defined lifecycle from qualification and commercial agreement through account setup, catalogue onboarding, launch, ongoing performance management and eventual exit.","audience":["Seller management","Marketplace operations","Commercial teams","Catalogue teams","Finance and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding the Seller Lifecycle":"\n<p>The Seller lifecycle is the complete journey through which a business becomes an active Seller and continues participating in your marketplace.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Identify and qualify</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Agree commercial terms</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Create and configure the account</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Connect and onboard products</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Validate and launch</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Manage performance</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Renew, pause or exit</strong></div></div>\n<p>Creating a Seller account is only one step. Launch readiness also requires product, shipping, Order, refund and finance workflows to operate successfully.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Track lifecycle stages operationally.</strong> Use Marketplacer account information together with your CRM or Seller onboarding tracker. Your internal lifecycle stages do not all need to be native Seller statuses.</div>\n","Recruit and Qualify Sellers":"\n<p>Qualify Sellers against the marketplace proposition before beginning detailed platform onboarding.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Review area</th><th>Questions to answer</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product fit</td><td>Does the range support the marketplace proposition and product policy?</td></tr><tr><td>Technical fit</td><td>Which system holds products, price and inventory, and can it use an approved connection method?</td></tr><tr><td>Operational fit</td><td>Can the Seller meet dispatch, tracking, cancellation, return and support expectations?</td></tr><tr><td>Commercial fit</td><td>Are the commission or wholesale model, fees, postage and Remittance terms achievable?</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Use a clear outcome such as <strong>Proceed</strong>, <strong>Proceed with conditions</strong>, <strong>Hold</strong> or <strong>Decline</strong>. Record risks, owners and target dates before progressing.</p>\n","Confirm Commercial and Operational Readiness":"\n<p>Confirm the Seller agreement and operating model before completing live account configuration.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Commercial model and Commission Package</li><li>Commission on postage, Merchant Fees and tax responsibilities</li><li>Remittance delay, payout approval and payout method</li><li>Launch Categories, Brands and product volume</li><li>Product source and ongoing update ownership</li><li>Shipping, dispatch, tracking, cancellations, returns and refunds</li><li>Operational, technical, finance and escalation contacts</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Align the account with the agreement.</strong> Configure only approved terms and document every Seller-specific exception.</div>\n","Create and Configure the Seller Account":"\n<p>Create and manage Seller accounts through <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers</code>. Search first to avoid duplicate legal entities, users or test accounts.</p>\n<p>Use a <strong>Prospective</strong> account where information is being prepared before the Seller is ready to trade. Use a <strong>Retailer</strong> account for the applicable selling and subscription configuration.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Verified business and legal information</li><li>Primary user and operational email addresses</li><li>Commission, Remittance and payout configuration</li><li>Orders, Advert Management, MConnect or API access</li><li>Product Vetting, notification and refund settings</li><li>Account Manager, tags, account code and lifecycle owner</li></ul>\n<p>Test login, MFA or SSO, Seller Portal visibility and notifications before product onboarding begins.</p>\n","Connect and Onboard the Product Catalogue":"\n<p>Choose the product-ingestion method according to the Seller's source system and operating capability.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Onboarding focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Seller Portal</td><td>Manual Advert and Variant creation</td></tr><tr><td>Bulk Product Management Multi Sheet</td><td>Category-specific creation with controlled dropdowns</td></tr><tr><td>Bulk Product Management Single Sheet</td><td>Broad catalogue creation or updates in one table</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect</td><td>Connection settings, product selection, mapping and synchronisation</td></tr><tr><td>API</td><td>Credentials, implementation, monitoring and fallback processes</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Complete Category, Brand, Advert Option Type, Variant Option Type and Option Value mapping. Resolve Catalog Rule failures and complete Product Vetting before approving the launch range.</p>\n","Validate and Launch the Seller":"\n<p>Use evidence-based launch gates covering commercial, account, catalogue, fulfilment, refund and finance readiness.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Create a controlled test Order</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Confirm the Seller Invoice and notification</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Create a Shipment and tracking</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Test a cancellation or return path</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Validate commission, fees and Remittance</strong></div></div>\n<p>Record the approved Advert and Variant counts, launch date, known exclusions, escalation owners and hypercare period.</p>\n","Manage the Active Seller":"\n<p>Move the Seller into a regular operating cadence after launch.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cadence</th><th>Review</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Daily</td><td>Urgent Orders, dispatch, tracking, Refund Requests, integration and customer incidents</td></tr><tr><td>Weekly</td><td>Catalogue errors, products awaiting action, performance exceptions and upcoming promotions</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly or quarterly</td><td>Sales, availability, fulfilment, returns, customer feedback, finance and growth</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Treat each new Category or major product range as a controlled mini-onboarding. Confirm taxonomy, mapping, shipping, Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and front-end publication before expansion.</p>\n","Remediate, Pause and Offboard":"\n<p>Use a documented improvement plan where a Seller repeatedly misses operational, catalogue or customer expectations.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Issue and evidence</li><li>Customer and business impact</li><li>Required Seller and Operator actions</li><li>Owners, targets and review dates</li><li>Consequence if the issue remains unresolved</li></ul>\n<p>Before pausing or deleting a Seller, resolve outstanding Orders, Refund Requests, returns, Seller Invoices, Remittances, integrations and customer enquiries.</p>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Complete operational closure before deletion.</strong> Deleting a Seller removes Seller Portal and API access and prevents the Seller from fulfilling outstanding Orders.</div>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004001312-Create-a-new-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a New Seller</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441867032717-Manage-Sellers-page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Sellers Page</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115006597508-Manage-seller-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Seller Accounts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599850695821-Intro-to-the-Seller-Performance-dashboard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Intro to the Seller Performance Dashboard</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-information","Seller Information to Collect"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"],["seller-performance","Seller Performance"],["seller-support-boundaries","Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries"]]},"seller-information":{"summary":"Collect and verify the business, contact, commercial, operational, catalogue, shipping and payout information needed to create and onboard each Seller accurately.","audience":["Seller onboarding","Marketplace operations","Finance","Catalogue teams","Technology and legal"],"sections":{"Understanding Seller Information Collection":"\n<p>Collect Seller information before account creation so the account, agreement, product connection and operating model use one verified source.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Issue a controlled questionnaire</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Validate the response</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Resolve gaps and conflicts</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Create the Seller account</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Ask the Seller to verify its details</strong></div></div>\n<p>Classify each field as required, optional, marketplace-specific or conditionally required. The exact account fields can vary by region and enabled features.</p>\n","Business Identity and Account Ownership":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Business Name and Legal Business Name</li><li>Registered entity and country</li><li>ABN, EIN, VAT or other approved identifier</li><li>Tax registration status</li><li>Primary Seller Portal user</li><li>Unique user email and preferred username</li><li>Company logo and approved Brand assets</li><li>Prospective or Retailer account stage</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use the exact legal entity.</strong> The Legal Business Name can appear on Marketplacer-generated Order, Invoice, commission and Remittance documents.</div>\n","Contacts and Notifications":"\n<p>Collect a role-based contact matrix rather than relying on one person for every onboarding and operational task.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Responsibility</th><th>Contact required</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Primary account owner</td><td>Name, email, phone and time zone</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue and integration</td><td>Product and technical contacts</td></tr><tr><td>Orders and fulfilment</td><td>Operational inbox, warehouse contact and hours</td></tr><tr><td>Returns and customer service</td><td>Support contact, SLA and escalation</td></tr><tr><td>Finance and payouts</td><td>Accounts contact and authorised payout contact</td></tr><tr><td>Commercial and executive escalation</td><td>Agreement owner and senior accountable contact</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Confirm which addresses receive Order, refund, Remittance, low-stock and integration notifications. Test shared inboxes and distribution lists before launch.</p>\n","Addresses, Fulfilment, Returns and Customer Policies":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Registered business address</li><li>Primary ship-from address and operating hours</li><li>Additional fulfilment locations</li><li>Return address and return-authorisation process</li><li>Collection or store locations where applicable</li><li>Carriers, tracking capability and dispatch cut-off</li><li>Shipping regions, exclusions and delivery services</li><li>Approved shipping, customer-service and exchange policies</li></ul>\n<p>Keep the registered, ship-from and return addresses distinct where they serve different purposes.</p>\n","Commercial, Tax and Payout Information":"\n<p>Collect financial information only after the commercial position has been approved.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Record</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Commercial</td><td>Commission or wholesale model, package, fees, postage, promotion funding and currency</td></tr><tr><td>Agreement</td><td>Version, signature, effective date, renewal, notice and approved exceptions</td></tr><tr><td>Tax</td><td>Registration country, identifier, exemptions and product-specific treatment</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance</td><td>Delay, schedule, approval, postage treatment and finance contact</td></tr><tr><td>Payout</td><td>Approved provider workflow, verification status and authorised owner</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Use secure financial workflows.</strong> Avoid collecting identity documents, passwords, access tokens or bank details through ordinary email or unprotected spreadsheets.</div>\n","Catalogue, Integration and Operational Readiness":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Launch Categories and Brands</li><li>Advert, Variant and SKU estimates</li><li>Representative product samples</li><li>Required attributes, images, barcodes and compliance information</li><li>Source ecommerce, ERP, PIM or inventory system</li><li>Seller Portal, Bulk Product Management spreadsheet, MConnect or API connection</li><li>Mapping volume and missing marketplace values</li><li>Inventory, Order, fulfilment, cancellation and refund capability</li></ul>\n<p>Estimate onboarding effort from product-data quality and integration complexity, not SKU count alone.</p>\n","Custom Fields, Documents and Data Protection":"\n<p>Use standard Seller fields wherever they fit. Use approved custom fields only for marketplace-specific business information with a defined owner and purpose.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Define the field type, accepted values and edit owner</li><li>Record where documents are stored and when they expire</li><li>Apply least-privilege access</li><li>Minimise the personal and sensitive information collected</li><li>Keep credentials and identity documents out of free-text fields</li><li>Record the source of truth and retention period</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Custom fields are not a document vault.</strong> Store agreements, certificates and regulated information in your approved secure repository.</div>\n","Collection Workflow, Validation and Readiness":"\n<ol><li>Define the information set from Marketplacer fields, the Seller agreement and your operating model.</li><li>Assign each field to the correct Seller or Operator owner.</li><li>Use one controlled submission method.</li><li>Validate the legal entity, users, commercial settings, addresses, product scope and payout route.</li><li>Resolve discrepancies before account creation.</li><li>Create the account and record the Seller ID.</li><li>Ask the Seller to verify Account Settings and operational contacts.</li><li>Complete a final launch review.</li></ol>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404678147853-Information-to-collect-from-sellers-for-onboarding\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Information to Collect from Sellers for Onboarding</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004001312-Create-a-new-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a New Seller</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31439944444813-About-Custom-Fields\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">About Custom Fields</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller Settings</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-lifecycle","Seller Lifecycle"],["seller-account-creation","Seller Account Creation"],["default-seller-configuration","Default Seller Configuration"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"]]},"seller-account-creation":{"summary":"Create each Seller account from verified information, select the appropriate account type, apply approved settings and confirm secure Seller Portal access before product onboarding begins.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Seller onboarding","Commercial teams","Finance","Technology and integrations"],"sections":{"Understanding Seller Account Creation":"\n<p>A Seller account connects the business identity, Seller Portal users, commercial settings, product access, fulfilment controls and internal ownership used throughout the Seller lifecycle.</p>\n<p>Create and manage accounts through <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers</code>. You can create one Seller or import multiple Sellers from a validated file.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Account creation is not launch approval.</strong> Access, products, mapping, shipping, testing, refunds and finance still need to be completed.</div>\n","Prepare Before You Create":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Search for an existing business, legal entity or user</li><li>Confirm Sandbox or Production</li><li>Verify Business Name, Legal Business Name and identifier</li><li>Confirm the primary user and unique login email</li><li>Confirm Business Email, ship-from address and operational contacts</li><li>Approve the account type and Commission Package</li><li>Review marketplace-wide Seller Settings</li><li>Record product connection, owner and target launch date</li></ul>\n<p>Use clearly labelled test accounts in Sandbox and keep live Seller emails out of testing unless the Seller has agreed to participate.</p>\n","Create an Individual Seller":"\n<p><code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Create New Seller</code></p>\n<ol><li>Open the creation form.</li><li>Complete Standard Information from the verified Seller record.</li><li>Select Prospective or Retailer.</li><li>Apply the approved initial commercial and account-feature settings.</li><li>Assign Account Manager, tags and account code.</li><li>Create the account.</li><li>Search for the new Seller and reopen the edit page.</li><li>Confirm no values reverted to an unexpected default.</li></ol>\n","Complete the Account Fields":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Account area</th><th>Review</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Standard Information</td><td>Business identity, legal name, user, emails, address, phone and region</td></tr><tr><td>Subscription and Commission</td><td>Account type, package, rates and applicable charges</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance Details</td><td>Approval, delay, schedule, postage and payout method</td></tr><tr><td>Account Features</td><td>Orders, Advert Management, MConnect, API, Vetting, notifications and refunds</td></tr><tr><td>Wholesale Preferences</td><td>Approved wholesale access and pricing ownership</td></tr><tr><td>Account Management</td><td>Account Manager, tags, code, rating and internal status</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Compare the final values with the Seller agreement and your configuration matrix.</p>\n","Control Access and First Login":"\n<p>Send the environment-specific Seller Portal URL and first-login guidance only after the account and primary user have been checked.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Welcome or password setup email received</li><li>Correct Seller account displayed</li><li>MFA or SSO completed where required</li><li>Expected menus visible</li><li>Additional Seller users created as individual accounts</li><li>Support and password-recovery route understood</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Test each environment separately.</strong> Sandbox access does not prove that Production access and configuration are correct.</div>\n","Import Multiple Sellers":"\n<p>Use <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Import Sellers</code> for a larger, standardised cohort.</p>\n<ol><li>Download the current template.</li><li>Retain an unchanged reference copy.</li><li>Populate verified values and exact accepted field formats.</li><li>Test one or two rows in Sandbox.</li><li>Review the created account settings and access.</li><li>Correct the source file before importing the full cohort.</li><li>Review failed rows and representative accounts.</li><li>Retain the final file and result.</li></ol>\n","Review and Configure After Creation":"\n<p>Open the Seller from <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers</code> and complete the full Seller-specific review.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Commission Package, Remittance and payout</li><li>Orders and Advert Management access</li><li>MConnect or API access</li><li>Product Vetting and catalogue controls</li><li>Dispatch SLA, notifications and tracking</li><li>Cancellation, refund and return-label settings</li><li>Onboarding tasks and Setup Requirements</li><li>Account Manager and current onboarding stage</li></ul>\n<p>Update the Seller onboarding tracker with the generated Seller ID, access status, current blocker and next action.</p>\n","Validate and Govern Seller Accounts":"\n<p>Audit Seller accounts before launch and periodically after launch.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Identity and legal details verified</li><li>Users and access tested</li><li>Commercial and payout settings approved</li><li>Account Features match the connection and operating model</li><li>Internal ownership and tags are complete</li><li>Sandbox and Production have been compared</li><li>Duplicate, abandoned and former Seller accounts are reviewed</li><li>High-impact account changes use an approval record</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004001312-Create-a-new-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a New Seller</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441867032717-Manage-Sellers-page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Sellers Page</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115006597508-Manage-seller-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Seller Accounts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/35320964961165-Configure-Multi-Factor-Authentication-for-sellers\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure Multi-Factor Authentication for Sellers</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004000232-Sign-into-your-account\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sign Into Your Account</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-information","Seller Information to Collect"],["default-seller-configuration","Default Seller Configuration"],["seller-portal","Seller Portal"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"]]},"default-seller-configuration":{"summary":"Define the standard commercial, access, catalogue, fulfilment, notification and refund settings applied to new Sellers, then document and test every approved exception.","audience":["Marketplace operations","Seller onboarding","Finance","Catalogue teams","Customer service and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Default Seller Configuration":"\n<p>Default Seller Configuration combines marketplace-wide settings under <code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings</code> with Seller-specific values under <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller</code>.</p>\n<p>Use the baseline for the standard Seller operating model. Apply an exception only where the agreement, connection, product risk, fulfilment model or payout route requires one.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Setting</th><th>Example baseline</th><th>Possible approved exception</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Product Vetting</td><td>Enabled</td><td>Disabled after a sustained quality review</td></tr><tr><td>Dispatch SLA</td><td>2 days</td><td>Longer for made-to-order products</td></tr><tr><td>Integration access</td><td>Disabled</td><td>MConnect or API enabled for an approved connection</td></tr><tr><td>Remittance delay</td><td>Marketplace default</td><td>Seller-specific contracted term</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Establish the Marketplace Baseline":"\n<p><code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings</code></p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Business identifier requirement and validation</li><li>Automatic ecommerce enablement</li><li>International Seller addresses</li><li>Commission on postage</li><li>Marketplace-generated Remittance and refund emails</li><li>Document presentation and marketplace branding</li><li>Marketplace dispatch SLA</li><li>Subscription, Remittance delay and Merchant Fee defaults</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Review irreversible features carefully.</strong> Complete the required technical and operational validation before enabling advanced financial capabilities.</div>\n","Configure Commercial and Remittance Settings":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Commission Package and effective date</li><li>Subscription settings where used</li><li>Automatically approve payouts</li><li>Custom Remittance delay and schedule</li><li>Include shipping cost in Remittance</li><li>Custom Merchant Fee overrides</li><li>Payout method and verification status</li><li>Wholesale preferences where approved</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Automatic approval does not bypass eligibility.</strong> The Seller Invoice must still satisfy completion, delay, schedule and financial-position conditions before the nightly Remittance process includes it.</div>\n","Configure Account Access and Integrations":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller model</th><th>Typical access</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Manual or spreadsheet Seller</td><td>Orders, Advert Management and Insights</td></tr><tr><td>MConnect Seller</td><td>Orders, Advert Management, Integrations Manager and Insights</td></tr><tr><td>API Seller</td><td>Orders, Advert Management, API access and operational fallback</td></tr><tr><td>Operator-managed catalogue</td><td>Approved Order and operational access only</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Apply least-privilege access. Enable Inquiries, Marketing, Multi Store, Markdown, MConnect or API only where the Seller's approved responsibilities require them.</p>\n","Configure Product and Catalogue Controls":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Require all products to be vetted</li><li>Catalog Rules and required product standards</li><li>Post-approval change monitoring</li><li>Daily low-stock report</li><li>Seller product limits</li><li>Golden Product or CPD controls where enabled</li><li>Commission Invoice visibility</li><li>Product source of truth and correction process</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Assess live catalogue impact.</strong> Enabling Product Vetting for a Seller with online products can take affected products offline until they are reviewed.</div>\n","Configure Orders, Fulfilment and Notifications":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Business Email, Email CC and SMS notifications</li><li>Tracking required for bulk dispatch</li><li>Approved Shipment Carriers</li><li>Marketplace or Seller-specific dispatch SLA</li><li>Packing-slip identity and price settings</li><li>Additional charges where part of the approved customer journey</li><li>Connected-system Order and Shipment synchronisation</li></ul>\n<p>Complete a fulfilment test covering Order notification, Seller Invoice, Shipment, carrier, tracking and the connected customer-facing update.</p>\n","Configure Cancellations, Returns and Refunds":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Allow Order cancellations before dispatch</li><li>Allow Sellers to initiate post-dispatch refunds</li><li>Return label enabled</li><li>Pre-dispatch, post-dispatch and denial Refund Reasons</li><li>Seller and customer communication ownership</li><li>Return-required and returnless operating rules</li><li>Operator customer-payment refund process</li></ul>\n<p>Test both a pre-dispatch cancellation and a post-dispatch return or refund, including Seller Invoice and Remittance adjustments.</p>\n","Apply Exceptions, Validate and Govern":"\n<p>Record each Seller-specific override with its reason, agreement reference, approval owner, effective date and review date.</p>\n<p>Use <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Show / hide table columns</code> to create a configuration-audit view for access, Vetting, notifications, payment and product state.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Sandbox workflow validated</li><li>Production account compared with the configuration matrix</li><li>One product and controlled Order tested</li><li>Post-launch configuration review scheduled</li><li>High-impact changes use approval and impact assessment</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25930591592973-Seller-settings\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Seller Settings</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/115006597508-Manage-seller-accounts\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Seller Accounts</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441867032717-Manage-Sellers-page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Sellers Page</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360040011851-Enable-and-use-the-returns-module\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Enable and Use the Returns Module</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570670327437-Configure-Seller-Performance-SLAs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure Seller Performance SLAs</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-account-creation","Seller Account Creation"],["seller-portal","Seller Portal"],["commission-packages","Commission Packages"],["remittances","Remittances"]]},"seller-portal":{"summary":"Prepare Sellers to use the Seller Portal for account setup, products, mapping, Orders, Shipments, Refund Requests, integrations, reporting and marketplace finance.","audience":["Seller onboarding","Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Finance","Customer service and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding the Seller Portal":"\n<p>The Seller Portal is the Seller-facing workspace used to manage marketplace activity, subject to the account access and features you enable.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Typical use</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Orders</td><td>Review Seller Invoices, dispatch Line Items and manage applicable refund actions</td></tr><tr><td>Products</td><td>Create, edit, map and troubleshoot Adverts and Variants</td></tr><tr><td>Imports & Exports</td><td>Run supported spreadsheet workflows</td></tr><tr><td>Insights & Statistics</td><td>Review sales, commission, Remittances and other enabled reports</td></tr><tr><td>Shipping</td><td>Manage approved Seller shipping settings</td></tr><tr><td>Extensions</td><td>Access MConnect, API keys and webhooks where enabled</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>The Seller Portal does not automatically become the source of truth for integrated Seller data. Document where each product, inventory, Order and fulfilment update should be made.</p>\n<div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Seller Portal walkthroughs</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c50cb388a0de434cb2937551ce7935eb?sid=3db7db0c-dc5b-4433-a937-764f7eee5795\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Intro to the Seller Portal</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/c1e4cc28dcdc414c9cf2e107563dc4cf?sid=262b7fe2-ad69-4cb9-b6fa-feb0b300ce0b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Logging into the Seller Portal</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/4fca4444d99c4d94b6900036b69f26b5?sid=4981c532-ccf5-4a66-aed4-0f3a1d5341b0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Left-hand menu walkthrough</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Access, Security and Seller Users":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Provide the correct Sandbox or Production URL</li><li>Confirm the primary user and unique login email</li><li>Complete password setup, MFA or SSO</li><li>Create individual users for catalogue, fulfilment, finance and technology</li><li>Review users when responsibilities change or the Seller is offboarded</li><li>Keep credentials and recovery codes secure</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Train against the enabled account.</strong> Not every Seller sees every menu area.</div>\n<div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Seller user walkthroughs</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/d59900dadba949fabb87275f5a549350?sid=8bcf922d-8bae-4407-a0f8-cc66feafcb96\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Creating multiple users</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/e34ec2dc36ef4c359b9c65be231e2e44?sid=09223cd6-0d0c-4a20-a8d1-2bb8415e554b\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>User Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Navigate the Seller Portal":"\n<p>Introduce the dashboard and navigation before detailed task training.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Dashboard attention items and Setup Requirements</li><li>Orders and outstanding fulfilment</li><li>Products, errors and mapping</li><li>Imports & Exports</li><li>Insights & Statistics</li><li>Marketing and Shipping where enabled</li><li>Extensions for MConnect, API and webhooks</li><li>User menu for Account Settings, Shipping Settings and users</li></ul>\n<p>Teach Sellers to open the underlying record rather than acting only from a dashboard notification.</p>\n","Complete Account Settings and Setup Requirements":"\n<p>Use the user menu to review Store Information, business details, policies, payment information, billing history and the assigned Commission Package.</p>\n<p>Seller Onboarding Processes appear under <strong>Setup Requirements</strong> and can direct the Seller to approved external activities such as payout verification, document signing or connection setup.</p>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Align policies before publication.</strong> Seller-entered shipping, service or exchange information should not conflict with the marketplace agreement or customer journey.</div>\n<div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Seller setup walkthroughs</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/a9ce63d98bd04523b7bf0029f705c063?sid=e8799e8e-5257-414a-b976-e72a07717a76\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Account Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/705744fb850341bdb769f19a4b6b7b6f?sid=27230c94-57d8-4ba8-be79-cc6c43935c8d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Business Page Settings</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/a08821a05acc45e2a0220d60de63df26?sid=37f48c5f-a4c2-41b2-a79f-a0005b35c0c6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Store Information</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Manage Products and Product Mapping":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Create and edit products under <code>Products &gt; Manage Products</code></li><li>Use Bulk Product Management Multi Sheet for Category-specific creation and controlled values</li><li>Use Bulk Product Management Single Sheet for broad creation or updates in one table</li><li>Connect supported ecommerce platforms through <code>Extensions &gt; MConnect</code></li><li>Map Seller Categories, Brands and attribute values</li><li>Resolve Catalog Rule and invalid Variant errors</li><li>Respond to Product Vetting feedback at the source of truth</li></ul>\n<p>For Shopify Sellers, correct source product data in Shopify where practical and re-import or synchronise the update.</p>\n","Manage Orders, Shipments and Refund Requests":"\n<p>Train operational users on the Marketplacer relationship between the customer Order, Seller Invoice, Line Item and Shipment.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Review outstanding Order</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Select Line Items and quantity</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Create Shipment</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Add carrier and tracking</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Verify connected-system update</strong></div></div>\n<p>Also train the approved pre-dispatch cancellation, post-dispatch return and Refund Request actions. The Operator remains responsible for the customer payment refund according to the marketplace process.</p>\n","Use Shipping, Extensions, Insights and Remittances":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Shipping Rules, Shipping Settings and Shipment Addresses where enabled</li><li>MConnect connection and error monitoring</li><li>API keys created under <code>Extensions &gt; API Access</code></li><li>Webhook endpoint ownership and monitoring</li><li>Sales and product reporting</li><li>Processed and unprocessed Remittances</li><li>Commission Invoices and Billing History where applicable</li></ul>\n<div class=\"callout warning\"><strong>Store API keys when they are created.</strong> Use descriptive key names, environment separation, secure storage and a revocation process.</div>\n<div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Seller operations walkthroughs</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/979e4841c45847aaa49a11a3be383178?sid=26d13a3a-57a8-49f0-bf8e-204049292f16\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Insights & Statistics</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/6d8f8c757f5848dcbe069a5b8b1b04a5?sid=5cf53558-cf40-4855-af36-a3bcc850b9a8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Remittance insights</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/d7d834ffa92e410fbdcfe4e987ff8b1d?sid=d2d0192d-d9ef-4375-bca3-fbd6c2c56f59\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Understanding Imports & Exports</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/cf388ba203304a55bf9f96a15c8c3034?sid=d24ed9c7-614c-49f5-bc96-342080c16030\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Extensions</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Train, Support and Govern Seller Portal Use":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Seller role</th><th>Training focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Primary account owner</td><td>Access, users, Account Settings and escalation</td></tr><tr><td>Catalogue user</td><td>Products, spreadsheets, mapping, Catalog Rules and Vetting</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment user</td><td>Orders, Shipments, tracking and cancellations</td></tr><tr><td>Customer-service user</td><td>Refund Requests and returns</td></tr><tr><td>Finance user</td><td>Seller Invoices, commission and Remittances</td></tr><tr><td>Technical user</td><td>MConnect, API, webhooks and monitoring</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Provide role-based resources and a clear Operator support route. Review active users, product errors, outstanding Orders, missing tracking, Refund Requests and integration health after launch.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10552716610829-Intro-to-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Intro to the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/32216806648461-Account-Settings-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Account Settings in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10611212114957-View-or-edit-a-product-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View or Edit a Product in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/41998926655373-Shopify-integration-for-sellers-Connect-to-Marketplacer\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Shopify Integration for Sellers: Connect to Marketplacer</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10607205218317-Generate-API-keys-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Generate API Keys in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/16409399992845-View-remittance-advice-summary-as-a-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View Remittance Advice Summary as a Seller</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-account-creation","Seller Account Creation"],["default-seller-configuration","Default Seller Configuration"],["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"],["seller-support-boundaries","Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries"]]},"seller-onboarding-process":{"summary":"Move each Seller from commercial approval to launch through a repeatable process covering account setup, access, products, mapping, testing, finance and launch approval.","audience":["Seller onboarding","Seller management","Marketplace operations","Catalogue teams","Finance and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding the Seller Onboarding Process":"\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Initiate and scope</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Collect and verify information</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Create and configure the account</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Provide access and training</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">5</span><strong>Connect and approve products</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">6</span><strong>Test complete operations</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">7</span><strong>Approve launch and hypercare</strong></div></div>\n<p>Seller Onboarding Processes in Marketplacer can provide Seller-facing Setup Requirements. Use them as part of the wider programme, while your onboarding tracker remains the source for stage, evidence, owners and blockers.</p>\n","Plan the Seller Onboarding":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Commercial model and Commission Package</li><li>Launch Categories, Brands and product count</li><li>Product, inventory and pricing sources of truth</li><li>Seller Portal, Bulk Product Management spreadsheet, MConnect or API method</li><li>Shipping, returns, customer-service and payout model</li><li>Target launch date and stage gates</li><li>Operator and Seller owners</li><li>Known risks, dependencies and phased scope</li></ul>\n<p>Choose an achievable representative launch range. Expand after the Seller proves its catalogue and Order operations.</p>\n","Prepare the Seller and Internal Teams":"\n<p>Provide one organised onboarding kit containing access guidance, taxonomy, product standards, mapping, Vetting, shipping, refund, finance and support information.</p>\n<p>Use the Seller kickoff to confirm responsibilities, connection, product scope, timeline, readiness gates and immediate actions.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Operator owner</th><th>Seller owner</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Account and commercial</td><td>Seller onboarding and commercial</td><td>Primary account owner</td></tr><tr><td>Products and mapping</td><td>Catalogue operations</td><td>Seller catalogue lead</td></tr><tr><td>Connection</td><td>Technology or integrations</td><td>Seller technical lead</td></tr><tr><td>Orders and returns</td><td>Marketplace operations and customer service</td><td>Seller fulfilment lead</td></tr><tr><td>Payout and finance</td><td>Finance</td><td>Seller finance contact</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Configure the Account and Seller Access":"\n<ol><li>Create the Seller from verified information.</li><li>Apply the approved Commission, Remittance, access, Vetting and refund settings.</li><li>Configure Setup Requirements where they add a useful Seller-facing action.</li><li>Send the correct environment URL and security guidance.</li><li>Confirm login, users, menus and account details.</li><li>Provide role-based training.</li><li>Record the Account Ready decision.</li></ol>\n","Connect Products and Complete Catalogue Onboarding":"\n<p>Start with representative products that test several Categories, Brands, Variant models, controlled Option Values and shipping requirements.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Connect the approved source or prepare the correct Bulk Product Management workbook</li><li>Complete Category, Brand and attribute mapping</li><li>Resolve missing marketplace values through the governed request process</li><li>Correct Catalog Rule failures</li><li>Complete Product Vetting</li><li>Assign Shipping Profiles</li><li>Validate price, inventory, images and front-end publication</li><li>Confirm ongoing update ownership</li></ul>\n","Test Orders, Fulfilment, Refunds and Finance":"\n<p>Complete an end-to-end test before live customer Orders are accepted.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Test</th><th>Confirm</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Order creation</td><td>Correct Seller Invoice, Line Items, price, postage, tax and notification</td></tr><tr><td>Fulfilment</td><td>Shipment, carrier, tracking, partial fulfilment and connected-system update</td></tr><tr><td>Inventory</td><td>Expected reduction and source-system behaviour</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation or return</td><td>Refund Request, communication and Seller financial adjustment</td></tr><tr><td>Finance</td><td>Commission, Merchant Fee, Remittance delay, schedule and payout amount</td></tr><tr><td>Support</td><td>Issue reaches the correct owner with record identifiers and evidence</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","Approve Launch and Manage Hypercare":"\n<p>Record launch approval only when mandatory commercial, account, catalogue, operational and finance evidence is complete.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Approved Advert and Variant count</li><li>Launch date and excluded scope</li><li>Account and product exceptions</li><li>First-Order monitoring owners</li><li>Integration, catalogue and customer escalation contacts</li><li>Daily hypercare checks</li><li>Post-launch review date</li><li>Business-as-usual handover owner</li></ul>\n","Track Progress, Escalate and Improve":"\n<p>Track each task by priority, owner, due date, status and evidence. Use stage gates such as Commercially Ready, Account Ready, Connection Ready, Catalogue Ready, Operationally Ready and Launch Ready.</p>\n<p>Escalate blockers early, especially agreement delays, incomplete information, connection credentials, mapping gaps, Product Vetting backlogs, missing Shipping Profiles and failed test Orders.</p>\n<p>Measure time in stage, first-pass product approval, mapping volume, test defects, time to first live product and time to first successful Order. Use the results to improve qualification, training, templates and Catalog Rules.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/32217510943245-Create-seller-onboarding-processes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create Seller Onboarding Processes</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/32217566099981-Access-seller-onboarding-tasks-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Access Seller Onboarding Tasks in the Seller Portal</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004001312-Create-a-new-seller\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Create a New Seller</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441867032717-Manage-Sellers-page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Sellers Page</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/10611212114957-View-or-edit-a-product-in-the-Seller-Portal\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">View or Edit a Product in the Seller Portal</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-lifecycle","Seller Lifecycle"],["seller-portal","Seller Portal"],["seller-support-boundaries","Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries"],["seller-launch-readiness","Seller Launch Readiness"]]},"seller-support-boundaries":{"summary":"Define who supports each Seller onboarding and operational activity, keep the Operator as the primary marketplace contact and escalate platform issues with complete evidence.","audience":["Seller onboarding","Seller management","Marketplace operations","Customer service","Finance and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries":"\n<p>Support boundaries identify who completes work, makes decisions, investigates issues and communicates with the Seller.</p>\n<div class=\"process-flow\"><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">1</span><strong>Seller contacts the Operator</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">2</span><strong>Operator triages and investigates</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">3</span><strong>Correct specialist owner acts</strong></div><div class=\"process-step\"><span class=\"step-number\">4</span><strong>Operator communicates the outcome</strong></div></div>\n<p>Your marketplace owns the Seller relationship. Explain the support model during recruitment and kickoff, including temporary assistance, source-of-truth ownership and the route for urgent issues.</p>\n","Define Operator and Seller Responsibilities":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Operator owns</th><th>Seller owns</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Marketplace policy, account configuration and taxonomy</td><td>Accurate business and source-system information</td></tr><tr><td>Catalog Rules, Product Vetting and launch approval</td><td>Product content, price, inventory and source-data corrections</td></tr><tr><td>Commission, Remittance and refund configuration</td><td>Fulfilment, tracking and approved return actions</td></tr><tr><td>First-line marketplace support and escalation</td><td>Timely evidence and participation in remediation</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Marketplace standards remain an Operator decision.</strong> Sellers can request Categories, Brands, terms or access, but the Operator approves the resulting marketplace configuration.</div>\n","Define Marketplacer and Partner Responsibilities":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li><strong>Marketplacer Delivery:</strong> platform onboarding, enablement, configuration guidance and implementation coordination according to the service engagement</li><li><strong>Marketplacer Support:</strong> investigation of Marketplacer platform behaviour after first-line triage</li><li><strong>System Integrator:</strong> customer-facing ecommerce, middleware, custom integrations and code it operates</li><li><strong>Seller source provider:</strong> source-store permissions, data, outages and third-party applications</li><li><strong>Payment or payout provider:</strong> authorisation, settlement, verification and transfer status</li></ul>\n<p>Do not assume every Operator receives the same post-launch service. The ongoing Marketplacer relationship depends on the applicable Business Services Agreement.</p>\n","Set Boundaries for Product and Integration Support":"\n<p>Define any initial product-onboarding assistance before work begins.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Included example</th><th>Seller retains responsibility</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>First representative product batch</td><td>Accurate source data and ongoing catalogue maintenance</td></tr><tr><td>Initial mapping support</td><td>Understanding and correcting Seller source values</td></tr><tr><td>One correction review</td><td>Future corrective uploads and source remediation</td></tr><tr><td>Connection walkthrough</td><td>Source credentials, permissions and operational monitoring</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>For API implementations, Marketplacer provides platform APIs and documentation. The Seller or its implementation partner owns design, development, retry handling, deployment, security and ongoing maintenance.</p>\n","Provide First-Line Triage and Self-Service":"\n<ol><li>Confirm Sandbox or Production.</li><li>Confirm the Seller and affected record identifiers.</li><li>Define expected and actual behaviour.</li><li>Review account and marketplace configuration.</li><li>Review Seller action and source data.</li><li>Check the relevant Marketplacer guidance.</li><li>Reproduce safely where practical.</li><li>Resolve internally or assign the correct specialist.</li></ol>\n<p>Provide role-based Seller guides for access, products, mapping, fulfilment, refunds, finance and integrations so common questions can be resolved consistently.</p>\n","Escalate Platform Issues to Marketplacer Support":"\n<p>Submit a Support request when triage indicates that documented Marketplacer behaviour may be failing or a platform record cannot progress as expected.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Include</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Environment and marketplace</td><td>Production and Operator Portal URL</td></tr><tr><td>Affected records</td><td>Seller, Advert, Variant, Order, Invoice, Refund Request or Remittance IDs</td></tr><tr><td>Timeline</td><td>Date, time, time zone and first occurrence</td></tr><tr><td>Expected and actual behaviour</td><td>Clear comparison</td></tr><tr><td>Troubleshooting</td><td>Configuration checked, actions repeated and safe reproduction</td></tr><tr><td>Impact and evidence</td><td>Seller count, customer impact, screenshots, file or request response</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Keep each request focused and exclude passwords, private API keys, payment details and unnecessary identity documents.</p>\n","Manage Communication, Service Levels and Handover":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Publish the Seller support route, hours and urgent escalation path</li><li>Separate first response from final resolution</li><li>Set service expectations by issue type</li><li>Translate technical updates into clear operational language</li><li>Keep the Operator as the Seller communication owner during Marketplacer investigation</li><li>End temporary onboarding help with an explicit handover date</li><li>Transfer open issues, exceptions and history into business-as-usual ownership</li></ul>\n","Govern Exceptions and Improve the Support Model":"\n<p>Classify repeated assistance as a standard marketplace service, time-limited onboarding service, contracted managed service or Seller responsibility.</p>\n<p>Review recurring login, product, mapping, integration, fulfilment, refund and Remittance questions. Convert repeated themes into clearer training, validation, Catalog Rules, templates or self-service guidance.</p>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplacer Support Centre</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/requests/new\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Submit a Marketplacer Support Request</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/categories/360006084971-Troubleshooting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Troubleshooting</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/31441867032717-Manage-Sellers-page\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Manage Sellers Page</a></li><li><a href=\"https://api.marketplacer.com/docs/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplacer API Documentation</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-onboarding-process","Seller Onboarding Process"],["seller-portal","Seller Portal"],["roles-responsibilities","Roles and Responsibilities"],["getting-support","Getting Support"]]},"seller-performance":{"summary":"Monitor Seller fulfilment, cancellations, returns and tracking, investigate the causes behind exceptions and use documented improvement plans to protect the customer experience.","audience":["Seller management","Marketplace operations","Customer service","Fulfilment teams","Commercial and technology"],"sections":{"Understanding Seller Performance":"\n<p>Seller Performance is the ongoing cycle of setting expectations, measuring outcomes, investigating exceptions and agreeing corrective actions.</p>\n<p>Open the dashboard through <code>Sellers &gt; Seller Performance</code>. It provides marketplace-wide and Seller-specific operational metrics, Seller Rating and data export.</p>\n<div class=\"callout note\"><strong>Use operational views for urgent incidents.</strong> Performance data is refreshed on a schedule and Seller Rating is recalculated weekly, so the dashboard is a trend and review tool rather than a live Order queue.</div>\n<div class=\"contextual-walkthroughs\"><h3>Platform walkthrough</h3><a class=\"contextual-walkthrough-link\" href=\"https://www.loom.com/share/1efa12948ca44a9e98aceabfa4c7b6a5?sid=715884d8-476d-4192-9f56-7082d3f4c77f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span>Seller Performance Dashboard</span><strong>Watch walkthrough</strong></a></div>","Configure Dispatch SLAs":"\n<p>Set the marketplace default through <code>Sellers &gt; Seller Performance &gt; SLA Configuration</code> or <code>Configuration &gt; Seller Settings</code>.</p>\n<p>Set an individual Seller override through <code>Sellers &gt; Manage Sellers &gt; Edit Seller &gt; Account Features</code>.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>The SLA measures the time to dispatch all applicable items</li><li>The timer begins from the payment timestamp</li><li>Weekends are excluded from the current calculation examples</li><li>Seller-specific values override the marketplace default for that Seller</li><li>Changes apply to new Orders placed after the update</li></ul>\n<p>Document the reason, agreement reference, effective date and review date for every Seller-specific exception.</p>\n","Read Marketplace-Wide Metrics":"\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Dispatch SLA breach rate</td><td>Orders where all applicable items were not dispatched within the configured timeframe</td></tr><tr><td>Return rate</td><td>Returned or refunded Line Items compared with Line Items sold</td></tr><tr><td>Cancellation rate</td><td>Cancelled Line Items compared with Line Items sold</td></tr><tr><td>Shipments without tracking</td><td>Shipments where the tracking area is empty</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Read the metrics together. A marketplace-wide increase across several Sellers may indicate a shared carrier, seasonal, configuration or integration issue rather than separate Seller failures.</p>\n","Read Seller Metrics and Rating":"\n<p>Review Order volume alongside percentages so a small number of events does not distort the interpretation.</p>\n<p>Current Seller Rating combines dispatch, cancellation, return and tracking performance over the available recent history and is recalculated weekly.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Platform information</th><th>Possible internal status</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Limited history or low Order volume</td><td>New</td></tr><tr><td>Stable strong performance</td><td>Performing</td></tr><tr><td>Emerging negative trend</td><td>Watch</td></tr><tr><td>Repeated breaches or customer impact</td><td>At Risk</td></tr><tr><td>Formal action plan active</td><td>Remediation</td></tr><tr><td>Targets met for the review period</td><td>Recovered</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"callout decision\"><strong>Use Rating as an indicator.</strong> Review Order volume, product mix, cancellation reasons and exceptional events before applying commercial or access controls.</div>\n","Investigate Performance Exceptions":"\n<p>Start with the affected metric, period, count, trend and customer impact, then review the underlying Orders, Seller Invoices, Line Items, Shipments, Refund Requests, products and integration activity.</p>\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Dispatch: payment time, applicable SLA, partial fulfilment and Shipment source</li><li>Cancellation: initiating party, reason, inventory, price and integration timing</li><li>Returns: reason, product content, Variant selection, picking, packaging and product quality</li><li>Tracking: carrier, tracking value, link validity, source system and customer update</li></ul>\n<p>Classify the cause as Seller process, Seller source data, marketplace configuration, Marketplacer platform, connected system, carrier, customer action, Operator action or external event.</p>\n","Manage Performance with Sellers":"\n<p>Explain performance expectations during onboarding and use evidence-based reviews after launch.</p>\n<ol><li>Review the agreed expectation and dashboard period.</li><li>Review rates and absolute counts.</li><li>Review affected Orders and products.</li><li>Confirm the root cause.</li><li>Agree Seller and Operator actions.</li><li>Set targets, due dates and the next review.</li><li>Record the consequence if the issue remains unresolved.</li></ol>\n<p>Apply proportionate controls such as increased monitoring, restricted range expansion, product removal, inventory correction or formal remediation. Provide a clear path to recovery.</p>\n","Export, Report and Establish an Operating Cadence":"\n<p>Use <code>Sellers &gt; Seller Performance &gt; Export all data</code>, then download the <code>sla_export</code> file from Imports & Exports.</p>\n<div class=\"data-table-wrap\"><table class=\"data-table\"><thead><tr><th>Cadence</th><th>Focus</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Daily</td><td>Outstanding Orders, dispatch deadlines, tracking and urgent customer incidents</td></tr><tr><td>Weekly</td><td>Recent breaches, cancellation and return exceptions, open actions and integration health</td></tr><tr><td>Monthly</td><td>Portfolio trends, tier changes, root causes and remediation</td></tr><tr><td>Quarterly</td><td>Sales, range, availability, customer feedback, commercial issues and growth</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n<p>Compare consistent periods and track current result, previous result, trend, marketplace comparison and target.</p>\n","Govern and Improve Seller Performance":"\n<ul class=\"check-list\"><li>Assign policy, dashboard, Order, return, catalogue, integration and escalation owners</li><li>Document metric definitions, targets, warnings and escalation thresholds</li><li>Apply context consistently across product type, volume and fulfilment model</li><li>Audit SLA overrides, tracking requirements and open action plans</li><li>Record previous and new SLA values with effective dates</li><li>Review marketplace-wide themes that may require a platform or process change</li></ul>\n<h3>Related Marketplacer articles</h3><ul class=\"check-list\"><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599850695821-Intro-to-the-Seller-Performance-dashboard\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Intro to the Seller Performance Dashboard</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570670327437-Configure-Seller-Performance-SLAs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Configure Seller Performance SLAs</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25570962112397-Marketplace-metrics\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Marketplace Metrics</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/25599997635341-Export-SLA-seller-data\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Export SLA Seller Data</a></li><li><a href=\"https://support.marketplacer.com/hc/en-us/articles/28925785268365-Operator-user-role-permissions\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Operator User Role Permissions</a></li></ul>"},"related":[["seller-lifecycle","Seller Lifecycle"],["seller-support-boundaries","Seller Onboarding Support Boundaries"],["seller-performance-reporting","Seller Performance Reporting"],["weekly-monthly-operations","Weekly and Monthly Operations"]]}};
